46
00:03:10,208 --> 00:03:12,625
Where's Suzuha?

47
00:03:12,625 --> 00:03:14,208
She just left, remember?

48
00:03:14,208 --> 00:03:15,542
What's gotten into you?

49
00:03:15,542 --> 00:03:17,208
I'll explain later!

50
00:03:19,833 --> 00:03:21,458
Crap!

51
00:03:21,458 --> 00:03:24,542
I forgot to ask what
time the guy showed up!

52
00:03:24,542 --> 00:03:26,542
Hey, how can I help you?

53
00:03:26,542 --> 00:03:28,458
Is that him?!

54
00:03:28,458 --> 00:03:34,625
He <i>does </i>have a barrel-ish,
balloon-ish silhouette...

55
00:03:34,625 --> 00:03:37,750
Daru?!

56
00:03:37,750 --> 00:03:39,833
Ack! Okarin?!

57
00:03:40,500 --> 00:03:42,458
Geez...

58
00:03:42,458 --> 00:03:44,958
Why would you make a
fake copy of the badge?!

59
00:03:44,958 --> 00:03:49,583
I'd feel bad if we never found
Miss Amane's old man, y'know?

60
00:03:49,583 --> 00:03:54,292
So I figured I could at least show
her the badge and make up a fake Titor!

61
00:03:54,292 --> 00:03:57,625
So you were gonna
give her false happiness?!

62
00:03:57,625 --> 00:03:59,792
Lies come in two types:

63
00:03:59,792 --> 00:04:02,208
lies that harm and lies that comfort--

64
00:04:02,208 --> 00:04:06,958
Do you honestly think Suzuha
would be happy if she found out?!

65
00:04:12,708 --> 00:04:18,125
Miss Amane told me
not to tell anyone, but...

66
00:04:18,125 --> 00:04:20,125
That time machine...

67
00:04:20,125 --> 00:04:23,167
...can only go backward in time.

68
00:04:24,375 --> 00:04:27,667
Once she leaves, there's no coming back.

69
00:04:33,167 --> 00:04:34,542
How's it going?

70
00:04:34,542 --> 00:04:36,708
For you.

71
00:04:36,708 --> 00:04:41,500
Oh! An ice-cold, no-calorie
cola is just what I needed!

72
00:04:41,500 --> 00:04:44,125
You're Mr. Nice Guy!

73
00:04:44,125 --> 00:04:46,667
Well? Do you think you can repair it?

74
00:04:46,667 --> 00:04:47,833
Should have it done by tomorrow.

75
00:04:47,833 --> 00:04:50,542
Wow! I know it's a rush job, but wow!

76
00:04:50,542 --> 00:04:52,917
Daru's got serious skills, all right.

77
00:04:52,917 --> 00:04:54,958
I told you, don't judge a book by its cover.

78
00:04:54,958 --> 00:04:55,833
Huh?

79
00:04:55,833 --> 00:04:58,167
You did?

80
00:04:58,167 --> 00:05:02,625
But you're right; he does seem so
unhealthy and drab on the outside!

81
00:05:02,625 --> 00:05:04,917
Yeah! I've changed my opinion of him!

82
00:05:04,917 --> 00:05:07,333
Then you can help me too, Miss Amane.

83
00:05:07,333 --> 00:05:10,833
And, inside the cramped time machine,
the sweltering heat will be so much

84
00:05:10,833 --> 00:05:12,833
that we'll forget our
embarrassment and strip our clothes...

85
00:05:12,833 --> 00:05:14,417
Have some self-respect, pervert!

86
00:05:14,417 --> 00:05:18,667
Daru-<i>kun </i>and Suzu-<i>san</i>
sure make a good match!

87
00:05:22,792 --> 00:05:25,875
Listen, I feel like I might never
get another chance to say this,

88
00:05:25,875 --> 00:05:28,583
so I'll just say it now...

89
00:05:28,583 --> 00:05:32,792
I'm really grateful to you all.

90
00:05:32,792 --> 00:05:37,375
When I first came to this time
period, I didn't know anyone,

91
00:05:37,375 --> 00:05:40,458
and even though this
era's so much more peaceful,

92
00:05:40,458 --> 00:05:44,250
I found it really frightening.

93
00:05:44,250 --> 00:05:48,083
But now I have so many friends.

94
00:05:48,083 --> 00:05:55,583
I really had a lot of fun, coming to
this era and spending time with you.

95
00:05:55,583 --> 00:05:59,417
Even if it was for a short time,
I'm glad to have been a fellow lab member.

96
00:05:59,417 --> 00:06:03,750
I'm glad... I could be with you guys.

97
00:06:03,750 --> 00:06:08,208
Once she leaves, there's no coming back.

98
00:06:08,208 --> 00:06:09,667
Okabe Rintaro!

99
00:06:09,667 --> 00:06:12,875
--Promise you'll--
--I <i>will </i>change the future!

100
00:06:12,875 --> 00:06:18,000
I'll make it a free world, like it is now!

101
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:19,292
Okabe Rintaro...?

102
00:06:19,292 --> 00:06:20,958
You don't...

103
00:06:20,958 --> 00:06:24,833
You don't regret making
memories with us, do you?

104
00:06:26,417 --> 00:06:29,292
If parting ways is inevitable...

105
00:06:29,292 --> 00:06:35,833
You don't regret being friends with
us and wish it never happened, do you?

106
00:06:35,833 --> 00:06:39,417
Wait, did Hashida Itaru tell you...?

107
00:06:39,417 --> 00:06:42,500
He's concerned about you too.

108
00:06:42,500 --> 00:06:44,750
I <i>am </i>going!

109
00:06:44,750 --> 00:06:47,583
Changing the future was my dad's--

110
00:06:47,583 --> 00:06:52,250
But don't you care what that'll mean for you?!

111
00:06:52,250 --> 00:06:57,083
The 70s aren't so bad either.

112
00:06:57,083 --> 00:07:00,042
I can make some
more friends like you guys

113
00:07:00,042 --> 00:07:02,208
and live a life of freedom!

114
00:07:10,167 --> 00:07:12,458
Here goes nothing!

115
00:07:16,708 --> 00:07:20,583
I think it should be okay now, but
you might wanna do one last check.

116
00:07:20,583 --> 00:07:22,250
Right!

117
00:07:25,125 --> 00:07:27,083
Yeah! It looks okay!

118
00:07:27,083 --> 00:07:30,042
You're really amazing!

119
00:07:30,042 --> 00:07:34,583
You should be happier!
You just fixed a time machine!

120
00:07:34,583 --> 00:07:38,708
What month and day in 1975 should I pick?!

121
00:07:38,708 --> 00:07:42,500
Should I go to a Capricorn day?
Or maybe an Aquarius day?

122
00:07:42,500 --> 00:07:44,042
No, that's for weddings!

123
00:07:44,042 --> 00:07:46,083
Oh, but an Aquarius day sounds good.

124
00:07:46,083 --> 00:07:49,208
You might make new
friends faster that way...

125
00:07:49,208 --> 00:07:52,458
Friends, huh?! I can't wait!

126
00:07:55,292 --> 00:07:58,542
"FG204"...?

127
00:07:58,542 --> 00:08:00,583
Say, Suzu-<i>san</i>!

128
00:08:00,583 --> 00:08:01,833
Yes?

129
00:08:01,833 --> 00:08:03,167
Is this...?

130
00:08:03,167 --> 00:08:08,250
Oh, that's the time machine's name!
My dad came up with it!

131
00:08:15,292 --> 00:08:18,125
M-My bicycle...?

132
00:08:18,125 --> 00:08:21,417
We thought it might fit
if we took the tires off!

133
00:08:21,417 --> 00:08:23,542
You're really fond of it, right?

134
00:08:25,458 --> 00:08:28,458
Yeah. I'll cherish it.

135
00:08:28,458 --> 00:08:31,000
Thank you.

136
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:32,875
Aha!

137
00:08:32,875 --> 00:08:37,750
Mayushii knows who
your father is, Suzu-<i>san</i>!

138
00:08:39,208 --> 00:08:40,042
--What?!
--Huh?!

139
00:08:40,042 --> 00:08:45,167
Not only that, he's right nearby!

140
00:08:45,167 --> 00:08:47,333
Wh-Where?!

141
00:08:47,333 --> 00:08:52,917
I kept thinking they were a
good match for some reason!

142
00:08:52,917 --> 00:08:58,750
But now I know it's because they're family!

143
00:08:58,750 --> 00:09:00,708
W-Wait! You're not saying...?!

144
00:09:00,708 --> 00:09:03,708
Suzu-<i>san</i>'s father...

145
00:09:03,708 --> 00:09:05,833
...is Daru-<i>kun</i>!

146
00:09:08,375 --> 00:09:09,333
Huh...?!

147
00:09:09,333 --> 00:09:11,833
That's not a funny joke!

148
00:09:11,833 --> 00:09:13,750
Besides, who would
ever marry <i>this </i>pervert--

149
00:09:13,750 --> 00:09:15,833
Whoa, no need to be mean!

150
00:09:15,833 --> 00:09:19,917
Explain! What led you to this conclusion?!

151
00:09:19,917 --> 00:09:23,375
First, "barrel" is "<i>taru</i>" in Japanese, right?

152
00:09:23,375 --> 00:09:25,667
<i>Taru</i>... Daru...

153
00:09:25,667 --> 00:09:26,917
Daru-<i>kun</i>!

154
00:09:26,917 --> 00:09:29,500
--Word play?!
--You call <i>that </i>a legitimate reason?

155
00:09:29,500 --> 00:09:33,708
But Suzu-<i>san</i>'s resistance
group was founded in part

156
00:09:33,708 --> 00:09:37,208
by Okarin and Barrel Titor-<i>san</i>, right?

157
00:09:37,208 --> 00:09:39,208
And the only one who'd know

158
00:09:39,208 --> 00:09:42,750
about your independent time
machine research in Akiba in 2010

159
00:09:42,750 --> 00:09:44,750
and that you have the Reading Stinger--

160
00:09:44,750 --> 00:09:46,333
"Reading Steiner."

161
00:09:46,333 --> 00:09:50,833
Yeah. The only one who'd know
about that is Daru-<i>kun</i>, right?

162
00:09:52,292 --> 00:09:56,500
And the best evidence of
all that Mayushii found is...

163
00:09:57,375 --> 00:09:59,333
The time machine's name?

164
00:09:59,333 --> 00:10:01,417
FG204.

165
00:10:01,417 --> 00:10:03,708
It's a Future Gadget!

166
00:10:03,708 --> 00:10:05,083
A Future Gadget?!

167
00:10:05,083 --> 00:10:09,167
And see the writing next to it too?

168
00:10:10,458 --> 00:10:16,500
Future Gadget 204, 2nd Edition, Version 2.31?!

169
00:10:16,500 --> 00:10:18,875
That naming style...!

170
00:10:28,292 --> 00:10:30,875
Dad...?

171
00:10:30,875 --> 00:10:34,375
A-At times like this,
you should call me "Daddy"!

172
00:10:34,375 --> 00:10:37,167
This is no time to act like a pervert!

173
00:10:44,250 --> 00:10:45,625
Dad...

174
00:10:45,625 --> 00:10:47,625
Y-Yeah.

175
00:10:47,625 --> 00:10:50,500
I came.

176
00:10:50,500 --> 00:10:53,292
I came to see you, Dad.

177
00:10:53,292 --> 00:10:56,917
In the time machine <i>you </i>built...

178
00:10:56,917 --> 00:10:58,583
Yeah...

179
00:10:58,583 --> 00:11:03,167
I <i>will </i>accomplish what you strived to do!

180
00:11:03,167 --> 00:11:05,333
So watch me.

181
00:11:05,333 --> 00:11:08,583
I-I will.

182
00:11:08,583 --> 00:11:10,875
I swear it.

183
00:11:18,875 --> 00:11:21,417
Incidentally...

184
00:11:21,417 --> 00:11:24,083
Was your mom cute?

185
00:11:24,083 --> 00:11:27,958
I'm hoping for someone short with
a baby face and humongous boobs...

186
00:11:30,875 --> 00:11:33,500
I think I'll keep it a secret!

187
00:11:36,333 --> 00:11:38,333
Well, I should probably get going.

188
00:11:38,333 --> 00:11:39,250
Yeah.

189
00:11:39,250 --> 00:11:42,875
Don't forget about us, now!

190
00:11:42,875 --> 00:11:43,958
Be careful.

191
00:11:43,958 --> 00:11:45,292
I'll be okay.

192
00:11:45,292 --> 00:11:49,000
I <i>will </i>get the IBN 5100, just you watch!

193
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:52,125
And then I'll get it into your hands!

194
00:11:52,125 --> 00:11:55,750
So, please, change the future.

195
00:11:57,875 --> 00:12:01,083
I'll see you again in 35 years!

196
00:12:01,083 --> 00:12:04,292
